 a riverbank or seashore."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: Bitter; Marion is the French form."],"variants":[{"name":"Marion","meanings":["Originally a medieval French diminutive form of   Marie  , introduced to Britain in the Middle Ages. In some places it was taken as a pet form of   Margaret   or   Margery .  As a male name, it is an altered form of the Continental male name <i>Marian</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>Marianus</i> (from   Marius  ), but is now rarely, if ever, used. It was the birth name of the American film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."]},{"name":"Marcia","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Margaret Clifton was born about 1419, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Robert Clifton. She married Thomas Englefield in 1431, in Englefield, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1456, at the age of 38."},"et":{"Abt 1419–       1456":"umbes 1419–1456","1419–1456":"1419–1456","1419–1464":"1419–1464","1438–1501":"1438–1501","–Male":"Surnud","       1456":"1456","1501":"1501","Abt 1419":"umbes 1419","1456":"1456","about 1438":"umbes 1438","1431":"1431","1464":"1464","1419":"1419","1438":"1438","Calne, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Calne, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Englefield, Berkshire, England":"Englefield, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bokenham Castle, Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1419–       1456":"noin 1419–1456","1419–1456":"1419–1456","1419–1464":"1419–1464","1438–1501":"1438–1501","–Male":"Kuollut","       1456":"1456","1501":"1501","Abt 1419":"noin 1419","1456":"1456","about 1438":"noin 1438","1431":"1431","1464":"1464","1419":"1419","1438":"1438","Calne, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Calne, Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Englefield, Berkshire, England":"Englefield, Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bokenham Castle, Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1419–       1456":"environ 1419–1456","1419–1456":"1419–1456","1419–1464":"1419–1464","1438–1501":"1438–1501","–Male":"Décédé","       1456":"1456","1501":"1501","Abt 1419":"environ 1419","1456":"1456","about 1438":"enviro